How-to-use virtual environments for MLND in my macOS

conda deactivate # if you see that your in base <conda> environment

python3 -m venv mlnd_env

source mlnd_env/bin/activate

# check that you r in mlnd_env package by looking for (mlnd_env)  # at the start of your terminal

# run the cmd below to verify the packages installed in this      # mlnd_env

mlnd_env/bin/pip freeze

